## Relationships

- A **{{TERM_1}}** has many **{{TERM_2}}**.
- A **{{TERM_2}}** belongs to exactly one **{{TERM_1}}**.
- A **{{TERM_3}}** is independent of both.

---

## Flagged ambiguities

> Resolved historical confusions. Keep these so you don't re-litigate them in 3 months.

- "{{OLD_TERM}}" was previously used to mean both X and Y — resolved on {{YYYY-MM-DD}}: X is now **{{TERM_1}}**; Y is now **{{TERM_2}}**.

---

## How agents use this file

- **`product-manager`** reads CONTEXT.md before scoping and writes all acceptance criteria in canonical terms.
- **`solution-architect`** reads CONTEXT.md before any design review and rejects designs that introduce new ambiguity.
- **`domain-expert`** owns this file — proposes new terms, resolves ambiguities, never deletes silently.
- **`grill-with-docs`** sharpens this file inline as a session runs. If you don't have Matt Pocock's skill installed, the equivalent grilling protocol is embedded in `/plan-feature`'s Step 0.

If the user says a term that conflicts with the glossary, agents are instructed to call it out immediately:

> "Your glossary defines 'cancellation' as X, but you seem to mean Y — which is it?"

That single behavior — agents pushing back on drift — is what makes this file pay for itself over multiple sessions.
